  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The Analgesia Nociception Index (ANI) is a new unitless marker derived from Heart Rate
      Variability spectral analysis, ranging between 0 and 100 and expressing the parasympathetic
      tone. The ANI is proposed as surrogate marker for the analgesia nociception balance. However,
      many perioperative factors such as medications, position, maneuvers may influence the ANI
      values and may lead to misinterpretation. Moreover the ability of the ANI to guide opioid
      dosing has never been tested. Therefore, the aim of our study is to collect in a database all
      the perioperative factors and to study their influence on the ANI.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
